{
  "texts": [
    "learned a compressed latent representation and by training a denoising autoencoder.",
    "Nonetheless, Watts et al. (2023) noted that neural vocoders which run in real-time on a CPU often rely on powerful CPUs, limiting use in low-resource environments.",
    "In particular, they highlight Alternative and Augmentative Communication (AAC) devices, which are used by people with speech and communication disabilities (Murray and Goldbart, 2009).",
    "Watts et al.",
    "proposed a method using the ISTFT and pitch-synchronous overlap add (PSOLA), with lightweight neural networks operating at rates below the audio sample rate."
  ]
}